      • submitIndexRequest

        public void submitIndexRequest(Yamcs.IndexRequest req,
                               int limit,
                               String token,
                               IndexRequestListener listener)
                        throws YamcsException
        Asynchronously submit an index request. When the request is processed the provided listener will receive callbacks.
        Parameters:
        req - the request to be executed
        limit - if greater than 0, the result will be limited to this number of records. If more records are available, the last call will provide a token which can be used for a subsequent request to get more data
        token - if this is a subsequent request, indicates a token which is used for continuation.
        listener - where to send the resulting data
        Throws:
        YamcsException - exception thrown if the service is not in running state or the the request is invalid
